FILM and television companies need greater incentives to encourage them to come to Scotland, says the national arts body. Tax breaks move to attract more films to Scotland FILM and television companies need greater incentives to encourage them to come to Scotland, says the national arts body.Creative Scotland has identified incentives for production companies - such as tax breaks for filming in Scotland - as one of its key priorities for the country's film sector for the next three years.Films such as World War Z, a zombie movie that starred Brad Pitt, and sci-fi thriller Under The Skin, which featured Scarlett Johansson, have been filmed in Glasgow, as well as the US TV series Outlander.Creative Scotland believes more can be done to boost the sector. 